# InfraFlux v2.0 - Hosts Configuration Guide

## 🎯 **Overview**
The hosts configuration system provides explicit, declarative control over every VM in your infrastructure. Instead of specifying counts and letting the system assign IPs and IDs sequentially, you define each host individually with full control over its properties.

## 📋 **Configuration Schema**

### **Complete YAML Structure**
```yaml
# hosts.yaml - Complete example with all options
version: "1.0"  # Schema version for future compatibility

# Global defaults (optional, can be overridden per-host)
defaults:
  domain: homelab.local
  dns:
    - 1.1.1.1
    - 1.0.0.1
  storagePool: local-lvm
  diskFormat: raw
  
# Cluster definitions
clusters:
  homelab:  # Cluster name
    # Network configuration (optional if using auto-discovery)
    network:
      gateway: 192.168.1.1  # Can be auto-discovered
      subnet: 192.168.1.0/24  # Can be auto-discovered
      bridge: vmbr0
    
    # Master nodes configuration
    masters:
      - name: k8s-master-01
        vmId: 8001
        ip: 192.168.1.201
        cores: 4
        memory: 8192  # MB
        disk: 50G
        tags:
          - production
          - primary-master
          - critical
        # Optional overrides
        storagePool: fast-ssd  # Override default
        
      - name: k8s-master-02
        vmId: 8002
        ip: 192.168.1.202
        cores: 4
        memory: 8192
        disk: 50G
        tags:
          - production
          - secondary-master
          
      - name: k8s-master-03
        vmId: 8003
        ip: 192.168.1.203
        cores: 4
        memory: 8192
        disk: 50G
        tags:
          - production
          - secondary-master
    
    # Worker nodes configuration
    workers:
      - name: k8s-worker-01
        vmId: 8101
        ip: 192.168.1.211
        cores: 8
        memory: 16384
        disk: 100G
        tags:
          - gpu
          - ml-workloads
          - high-memory
        # Custom hardware specs
        gpu:
          type: passthrough
          device: "0000:01:00.0"
          
      - name: k8s-worker-02
        vmId: 8102
        ip: 192.168.1.212
        cores: 4
        memory: 8192
        disk: 50G
        tags:
          - general
          - web-workloads
          
      - name: k8s-worker-03
        vmId: 8103
        ip: 192.168.1.213
        cores: 6
        memory: 12288
        disk: 75G
        tags:
          - database
          - persistent-workloads
        # Custom disk configuration
        additionalDisks:
          - size: 200G
            storagePool: bulk-storage
            purpose: database-data
    
    # Future: Infrastructure VMs (non-Kubernetes)
    infrastructure:
      - name: postgres-01
        vmId: 8201
        ip: 192.168.1.221
        cores: 4
        memory: 16384
        disk: 50G
        type: database
        os: ubuntu-22.04  # Future: different OS templates
        tags:
          - database
          - postgresql
          - critical
        
      - name: monitoring-01
        vmId: 8202
        ip: 192.168.1.222
        cores: 2
        memory: 4096
        disk: 30G
        type: monitoring
        tags:
          - monitoring
          - prometheus
          - grafana

# Multiple cluster support (future)
# clusters:
#   staging:
#     masters: [...]
#     workers: [...]
```

